{"bill":{"bill_id":1651794,"change_hash":"4edb1225a3f3c2dff9f5bb3bee3a5f56","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB1142\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB1142","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-02","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-10","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-31","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-02","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-08","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-09","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-09","event":9}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB1142","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"Sports betting; adjusted gross revenue, definitions.","description":"Sports betting; adjusted gross revenue. Reduces the exclusion from a sports betting permit holder's adjusted gross revenue, on which it is taxed, all cash and the cash value of merchandise paid out as winnings to bettors, and the value of all bonuses or promotions provided to bettors as an incentive to place or as a result of their having placed Internet sports betting wagers, by eliminating such exclusion for the first 12 months of sports betting activity for a permit holder, and subsequently limiting such exclusion to no more than 1.75 percent of the total amount of all sports betting wagers placed with that permit holder each month after the first 12 months of sports betting activity for a permit holder. Under current law, pursuant to the 2022 Special Session I appropriation act, after the first 12 months of sports betting activity, a permit holder is prohibited from excluding from adjusted gross revenue any bonuses or promotions provided to bettors as an incentive to place or as a result of their having placed Internet sports betting wagers. Sports betting; adjusted gross revenue. Reduces the exclusion from a sports betting permit holder's adjusted gross revenue, on which it is taxed, all cash and the cash value of merchandise paid out as winnings to bettors, and the value of all bonuses or promotions provided to bettors as an incentive to place or as a result of their having placed Internet sports betting wagers, by eliminating such exclusion for the first 12 months of sports betting activity for a permit holder, and subsequently limiting such exclusion to no more than 1.75 percent of the total amount of all sports betting wagers placed with that permit holder each month after the first 12 months of sports betting activity for a permit holder. Under current law, pursuant to the 2022 Special Session I appropriation act, after the first 12 months of sports betting activity, a permit holder is prohibited from excluding from adjusted gross revenue any bonuses or promotions provided to bettors as an incentive to place or as a result of their having placed Internet sports betting wagers.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-10","committee_id":164,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Finance and Appropriations"},{"date":"2023-02-08","committee_id":153,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"General Laws"},{"date":"2023-02-09","committee_id":147,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Appropriations"},{"date":"2023-02-10","committee_id":3850,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Appropriations: General Government & Capital Outlay"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23101704D","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Referred to Committee on Finance and Appropriations","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-31","action":"Reported from Finance and Appropriations with substitute (11-Y 4-N)","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1